    "claim": "The contract grants ERC20 allowances to arbitrary `claimLockup.tokenLocker` and `donation.tokenLocker` addresses without checking that they are trusted locker contracts, and it never revokes unused approval. An attacker can set the locker to their own EOA or malicious contract and directly `transferFrom` tokens out of `ClaimCampaigns`.",
    "impact": "This enables permissionless theft of escrowed funds. Because approvals are granted from the single shared `ClaimCampaigns` balance, the attacker can drain not only their own campaign deposit but also unrelated campaigns that use the same token, and any leftover allowance after cancellation remains as a latent backdoor over future deposits.",
    "paths": [
